Proud Claw of the Skathris Ven'Sho </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ifrinnofthebrood>Ifrinn of the brood</A> at: 6/10/03 7:19 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kurley>Kurley</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 802<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/10/03 8:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1566.topic&index=70>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Matrix Reloaded</span><hr size=1> &quot;Hmm.. I like the lipstick theory Kuladen. Just because I found that scene odd and not really fitting with the rest of the movie. The beautiful rich bored wife stereotype. Or perhaps its purpose was just to show how little humanity has changed, lovers quarrel are still an integral part of things? Or perhaps she was just jealous of Trinity and we're reading too much into it. Or perhaps they just wanted to show more of Neo-Trinity'. I'd really like to know more of Merovingian and Persiphone. Not being a history buff, can someone fill me in?&quot;<br>
<br>
If you listen carefully during that scene, apparently you can hear a sound similar to the &quot;modem&quot; sound that occurred when the trace program in the first Matrix movie was replicating on Neo (ie. the mirror covering him).  Notice also, the redness of her lipstick, which correlates to the &quot;red pill&quot; Neo took to activate the trace program and the &quot;red candy&quot; the Oracle offered to Neo.<br>
<br>
There's definitely something to the kiss, outside of the device of showing Trinity's affection for Neo and the fact that Persephone has lived without true love and passion for a long time.<br>
<br>
Now for the symbolism of the Merovingian and Persephone.  The Merovingian's were Frankish nobles who believed they were the direct descendants of Jesus Christ.  The Merovingian in the Matrix is a highly developed program &quot;from somewhere else&quot; outside of the Matrix, who came to the Matrix with the aim of controlling it, believing that he is a descendant of the &quot;singular artificial intelligence&quot; that humanity spawned which lead them to where they are now.<br>
<br>
Persephone is a persona in Greek mythology who was duped into entering the underworld, wherein she was imprisoned until the God intervened thereby allowing her to escape for half of the year (spring and summer I believe).  During fall and winter, Persephone was relegated to entering the underworld again.  <br>
<br>
Through this myth, the Wachowski's portray the Merovingian as the lord of the underworld (which is he quite clearly in the movie) to whom all things of darkness pay allegiance and find safety - evidenced by the werewolf, ghost and vampire exiled programs in his employ.  The lord of the underworld symbolism is made even clearer, as the &quot;lord&quot; in the Persephone myth kept her imprisoned by retaining all of the keys to the underworld - in the Matrix he has control over the Keymaker.<br>
<br>
There is some talk about Persephone being what is known as &quot;the Engineer&quot; of the Matrix.  Whether this is true or not, is a matter of speculation that'll be resolved in Revolutions.  The kiss must have some relevance, but I'm skeptical that it has anything to do with Neo's &quot;real world&quot; powers (ie. his disabling the squids)<br>
<br>
Which brings us to the supposition that Zion exists in the real world.  I've looked at both sides of the arguement, that Zion is indeed the real world and that Zion is simply another layer of the Matrix (the scorched earth Matrix as it were) and I honestly dunno - there is strong evidence for either arguement.<br>
<br>
Personally, I feel that layering the Matrix would be rather complex and hard to tie-off in one movie, but the Wachowski's are clever.<br>
<br>
&quot;I had not picked up on the 314 seconds being Pi, cool. And yes I found the subtle use of werewolves/vampires comical. I loved the keymaker *smile*&quot;<br>
<br>
The Pi thing is neat and makes sense.  The Matrix was created with a lock and a key, or a puzzle and a missing piece, which represents Pi.  The Architect knows about the missing piece/problem &quot;the anomoly&quot; but doesn't know where to look for the solution/missing piece.  The Oracle knows what the missing piece is, but doesn't want to tell the Architect because that would completely enslave humanity.<br>
