<br>
If so Neo does retain his powers in the real world. To me this symbolizes that our dreams really can come true.<br>
<br>
I got the Merovingian/Persephone story pretty much as the last poster suggested, but I am still baffled by the use of the Merovingian as the name for the lord of the underworld.<br>
<br>
From &quot;Holy Blood - Holy Grail&quot; and on the use of the Merovingians in modern conspiracy theory is very conspicuos. Most often they are portrayed as the descendants of Christ. Why would the genetic inheritor of the Christ role be &quot;evil&quot; while the spiritual inheritor (Neo) is &quot;good&quot;.<br>
<br>
Must be lacking som piece here.<br>
<br>
And that said we are still lacking the single biggest piece of them all. WHY is Morpheus' ship named Nebuchadnezzar? Nebuchadnezzar was the Babylonian king who held the Jews in slavery, why would the name be used to denotate something used to defend Sion?<br>
<br>
<br>
Also a small prediction: Morpheus will be shown to have greater powers inside the Matrix than we so far have been led to believe, he is after all the God of Sleep.<br>
